---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import JsonLd from '../components/JsonLd.astro';

const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'What is Jules?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'Jules is a deeply customized Claude Code operational system that runs a solo business. It handles content pipelines, research, scheduling, reporting, and code. It has defined personality, decision authority, and autonomous operational capability.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How is Jules configured?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'Jules has 18 custom skills, 5 hooks (including a unified safety guard), Cloud scheduled batch tasks, Telegram access, and a CLAUDE.md under 500 lines. v4 simplified the system dramatically while maintaining the same capabilities.',
      },
    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'Can I build something like Jules?',
      acceptedAnswer: {
        '@type': 'Answer',
        text: 'Yes. Jules is built entirely with Claude Code\'s built-in features: CLAUDE.md files, skills, hooks, and MCP servers. No external frameworks. The full source is available on GitHub. Start with a solid CLAUDE.md, add skills for repeated workflows, and build up from there.',
      },
    },
  ],
};
---

<Base
  title="Jules"
  description="Jules is an AI operational system that runs a solo business. 18 skills, 5 hooks, cloud batch automation, Telegram access. Open source, built on Claude Code."
  schema={faqSchema}
>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Jules</h1>

    <p>
      Jules is the AI system that runs my business. Not a chatbot. Not a wrapper around a prompt. An operational system that handles content pipelines, research, scheduling, code, reporting, and decision-making across my entire solo operation.
    </p>

    <p>
      It's built entirely on Claude Code's native features. No external frameworks, no custom runtimes. Skills, hooks, a CLAUDE.md, and MCP servers. That's the whole stack.
    </p>

    <p>
      The source is open: <a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/jules">github.com/jonathanmalkin/jules</a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Dashboard: Jules System Stats -->
  <section class="dashboard">
    <div class="dashboard-header">
      <h2>System Overview <span class="pulse">LIVE</span> <span class="version-badge">v4</span></h2>
      <p class="dashboard-sub">Same capabilities as earlier versions. Half the complexity.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="stat-grid">
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-number">18</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Skills</div>
        <div class="stat-detail">Consolidated workflows: /think, /build, /write, /research, /debug. Skill-to-skill chaining.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-number">5</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Hooks</div>
        <div class="stat-detail">Unified safety guard, RTK token optimization, desktop notifications, session-start sync.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-number always-on">ON</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Cloud Batch</div>
        <div class="stat-detail">Overnight: daily retro, morning briefing assembly, email fetch. Ready before the laptop opens.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-number always-on">ON</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Telegram</div>
        <div class="stat-detail">Interactive access from phone when laptop is open. Cloud web sessions when it's not.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-number">60-90%</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Token Savings</div>
        <div class="stat-detail">RTK (Rust Token Killer) rewrites dev commands for massive context savings.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="stat-card">
        <div class="stat-number">&lt;500</div>
        <div class="stat-label">Lines in CLAUDE.md</div>
        <div class="stat-detail">Rules absorbed into one file. Identity, routing, authority, safety. Always loaded.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container">

    <h2>What Makes It Different</h2>

    <p>
      Most Claude Code setups are a CLAUDE.md and a few prompts. Jules is a full operational system:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Identity and voice.</strong> Five defined registers (quick reply, technical, advisory, serious, excited) with anti-patterns that prevent corporate chatbot drift.</li>
      <li><strong>Decision authority.</strong> A formal framework: what Jules handles autonomously, what requires approval, and how the boundary shifts over time through standing orders.</li>
      <li><strong>Consolidated skills.</strong> 18 skills that do real work. /think for strategy, /build for software, /write for content, /research for deep investigation. Each is a multi-phase workflow, not a single prompt.</li>
      <li><strong>Unified safety guard.</strong> One hook script with four sections: command blocking, secret scanning, financial data guard, domain blocking. Deterministic. Fires on every tool call.</li>
      <li><strong>Cloud overnight batch.</strong> Daily retro, morning briefing assembly, email fetch. Runs on Anthropic Cloud. No VPS, no Docker, no daemon.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Architecture Diagram -->
    <h2>How It Works</h2>

    <div class="layer-stack">
      <div class="layer-bar layer-products">
        <span class="layer-icon">&#9881;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="layer-name">Products</div>
          <div class="layer-desc">Assessment tools, website, content pipeline. Applications the system builds and ships.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="layer-bar layer-automation">
        <span class="layer-icon">&#9200;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="layer-name">Automation</div>
          <div class="layer-desc">Cloud overnight batch, session-start sync, Telegram access.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="layer-bar layer-infra">
        <span class="layer-icon">&#128736;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="layer-name">Infrastructure</div>
          <div class="layer-desc">5 hooks: unified safety guard, RTK token optimization, notifications.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="layer-bar layer-config">
        <span class="layer-icon">&#9881;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="layer-name">Configuration</div>
          <div class="layer-desc">18 skills, CLAUDE.md. Request routing, research, planning.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="layer-bar layer-state">
        <span class="layer-icon">&#128203;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="layer-name">Operational State</div>
          <div class="layer-desc">Terrain, daily briefings, decision queue. Live working state that evolves daily.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="layer-bar layer-identity">
        <span class="layer-icon">&#129418;</span>
        <div>
          <div class="layer-name">Identity</div>
          <div class="layer-desc">Agent personality, user context, goals, voice registers, decision authority.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Architecture -->
    <h2>Architecture</h2>
    <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem;">Mac for interactive development. Cloud for scheduled tasks. No VPS, no Docker, no daemons.</p>
    <div class="hybrid-arch">
      <div class="hybrid-node hybrid-mac">
        <div class="hybrid-label">Mac</div>
        <div class="hybrid-detail">Interactive dev</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hybrid-arrow">&rarr;</div>
      <div class="hybrid-node hybrid-github">
        <div class="hybrid-label">Cloud</div>
        <div class="hybrid-detail">Overnight batch</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hybrid-arrow">&rarr;</div>
      <div class="hybrid-node hybrid-vps">
        <div class="hybrid-label">Telegram</div>
        <div class="hybrid-detail">Phone access</div>
      </div>
      <div class="hybrid-arrow">&rarr;</div>
      <div class="hybrid-node hybrid-phone">
        <div class="hybrid-label">Cloud Web</div>
        <div class="hybrid-detail">Remote sessions</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- A Day with Jules -->
    <h2>A Day with Jules</h2>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">Session start</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Auto-sync.</strong> Hook pulls latest code from GitHub on every session open.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">Sessions</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Real-time collaboration.</strong> Interactive terminal or VS Code. Skills route requests, hooks guard every tool call.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">Anytime</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Telegram from phone.</strong> Message Jules when the laptop is open. Cloud web sessions when it's not.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">Overnight</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Cloud batch.</strong> Retro + memory analysis, morning briefing assembly, email fetch. Ready before the laptop opens.
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-time">Wrap-up</div>
        <div class="timeline-content">
          <strong>Session report.</strong> Commit code, update memory, run quality checks, flag publishable content.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Version Evolution -->
    <h2>How Jules Evolved</h2>
    <div class="version-strip">
      <div class="version-col">
        <div class="version-tag">v1</div>
        <div class="version-title">Identity + Skills</div>
        <p>Personality, voice registers, decision authority. CLAUDE.md files and early skill workflows.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="version-col">
        <div class="version-tag">v2-v3</div>
        <div class="version-title">Automation + Planning</div>
        <p>Container infrastructure, scheduled jobs, planning dispatch, research agents, security hooks.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="version-col version-col-current">
        <div class="version-tag">v4</div>
        <div class="version-title">Simplification</div>
        <p>32 skills became 18. 15 hooks became 5. VPS eliminated. Cloud batch + Telegram. Same power, half the parts.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- The Simplification Story -->
    <h2>The Simplification Story</h2>

    <p>
      Jules grew to 32 skills, 20+ rules, 15 hooks, a Docker container with 9 cron jobs, and a Slack daemon. It worked, but the maintenance overhead was real. v4 asked: what if the system got more powerful by getting smaller?
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>/think</strong> replaced decompose + advisory. One skill handles all strategic thinking.</li>
      <li><strong>/build</strong> replaced scope + writing-plans + executing-plans + subagent-driven-development. One skill handles all software work.</li>
      <li><strong>safety-guard.sh</strong> replaced 6 hook scripts + 4 subscripts. One file, four sections, same protection.</li>
      <li><strong>Cloud batch</strong> replaced a VPS, Docker, 9 cron jobs, and an auth infrastructure. One scheduled task.</li>
      <li><strong>CLAUDE.md</strong> absorbed 20+ rule files. One file that loads every session.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Complexity is easy to add and hard to remove. The simplification made the system faster, more reliable, and easier to reason about.</p>

    <!-- Build Your Own -->
    <h2>Build Your Own</h2>
    <div class="getting-started">
      <p class="getting-started-lead">You don't need dozens of configurations to start. Try this one prompt:</p>
      <pre><code>claude "Read my codebase. Create a .claude/CLAUDE.md that describes
the project, key conventions, and common workflows. Then create
one skill in .claude/skills/ for the task I do most often."</code></pre>
      <p class="getting-started-sub">
        That's it. One CLAUDE.md and one skill. Build up from there.
        <br>Full source: <a href="https://github.com/jonathanmalkin/jules">github.com/jonathanmalkin/jules</a>
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>Read More</h2>

    <p>
      I write about how Jules works, what I've learned building it, and how the system evolves: <a href="/articles/">Articles &rarr;</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</Base>
